title: Grid Layout
subtitle: A powerful layout system available in CSS that allows for the two-dimensional arrangement of elements on a web page

title: Flexbox
subtitle: Officially known as the CSS Flexible Box Layout Module, is a powerful, efficient layout model designed to distribute space along a single column or row within a container.

title: CSS
subtitle: CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML (including XML dialects such as SVG or XHTML)

title: AVL Tree
subtitle: An AVL tree is a type of binary search tree (BST) that maintains a balance condition to ensure that the tree remains approximately balanced, meaning the depth of the two subtrees of any node differ by no more than one.

title: Red Black Tree
keywords: Red Black Tree, Binary Search Tree
subtitle: A Red-Black Tree is a type of self-balancing binary search tree, a data structure used in computer science to organize pieces of comparable data, such as numbers. It is an enhanced version of a binary search tree

title: Print Binary Tree
subtitle: Print binary tree in terminal in a intuitive way.

title: gRPC
subtitle: gRPC (gRPC Remote Procedure Call) is an open-source framework developed by Google for enabling efficient and scalable communication between services. It is designed to work across different languages and platforms
